    "# ==========================================================\n",
    "#  Real-Time Pencil Sketch & Oil Pastel Webcam Filter\n",
    "# ==========================================================\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 1: Install Required Libraries\n",
    "!pip install opencv-python numpy\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 2: Import Libraries\n",
    "import cv2\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# ------------------ Step 3: Start Webcam -------------------\n",
    "cap = cv2.VideoCapture(0)  # 0 for default webcam\n",
    "\n",
    "if not cap.isOpened():\n",
    "    raise IOError(\"Cannot access webcam.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Press 'q' to quit the webcam filter.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "while True:\n",
    "    ret, frame = cap.read()\n",
    "    if not ret:\n",
    "        break\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Resize for faster processing (optional)\n",
    "    frame = cv2.resize(frame, (640, 480))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # ---------------- Pencil Sketch Effect ----------------\n",
    "    gray = cv2.cvtColor(frame, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n",
    "    inverted_gray = 255 - gray\n",
    "    blurred = cv2.GaussianBlur(inverted_gray, (21,21), 0)\n",
    "    pencil_sketch = cv2.divide(gray, 255 - blurred, scale=256)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # ---------------- Oil Pastel Effect ----------------\n",
    "    oil_pastel = cv2.stylization(frame, sigma_s=150, sigma_r=0.25)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # ---------------- Combine Views ----------------\n",
    "    # Stack original, pencil sketch, and oil pastel horizontally\n",
    "    pencil_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(pencil_sketch, cv2.COLOR_GRAY2BGR)\n",
    "    combined = np.hstack((frame, pencil_rgb, oil_pastel))\n",
    "\n",
    "    cv2.imshow('Original | Pencil Sketch | Oil Pastel', combined)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Press 'q' to exit\n",
    "    if cv2.waitKey(1) & 0xFF == ord('q'):\n",
    "        break\n",
    "\n",
    "# Release webcam and close windows\n",
    "cap.release()\n",
    "cv2.destroyAllWindows()\n"
   ]
